narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: DO NOT TAKE THIS COURSE unless you absolutely have to for the language requirement. If you are beginning a language, begin with something other than Spanish, at least until fundamental changes are made to the spanish curriculum at Yale.
I only took it to fulfill the language requirement. I didn't like the class at all and I hate the language requirement at yale.
Yeah it's a good stepping stone on to the next levels.
I only took the course because I had to, and I would not recommend it to anyone else unless they have to.
This is a great class for maintaining your Spanish skills and expanding on material from L1 and L2. You will be more conversant afterwards. You will also get some exposure to Spanish culture.
